79 template <typename T> class handle_traits {};
80 
94 template <typename T, typename traits=handle_traits<T>> class handle {
95 private:
96  static mkldnn_status_t dummy_destructor(T){ return mkldnn_success; }
97 
98  std::shared_ptr<typename std::remove_pointer<T>::type> _data;
99  handle(const handle &&) = delete;
100  handle &operator=(const handle &&other) = delete;
101 protected:
102  bool operator==(const T other) const { return other == _data.get(); }
103  bool operator!=(const T other) const { return !(*this == other); }
104 public:
108  handle(T t, bool weak = false): _data(0) {
109  reset(t, weak);
110  }
111 
121  handle(): handle((T)0, true) {}
122 
123  handle(const handle &other): _data(other._data) {}
124  handle &operator=(const handle &other) {
125  _data = other._data;
126  return *this;
127  }
131  void reset(T t, bool weak = false) {
132  _data.reset(t, weak ? &dummy_destructor : traits::destructor);
133  }
134 
136  T get(bool allow_emtpy = false) const {
137  T result = _data.get();
138 
139  if (allow_emtpy == false && result == nullptr)
140  throw mkldnn::error(mkldnn_invalid_arguments,
141  "attempt to use uninitialized object");
142 
143  return result;
144  }
145 
146  bool operator==(const handle &other) const { return other._data.get() == _data.get(); }
147  bool operator!=(const handle &other) const { return !(*this == other); }
148 };

401 #define MKLDNN_DEFINE_BITMASK_OPS(enum_name) \
402 inline enum_name operator|(enum_name lhs, enum_name rhs) { \
403  return static_cast<enum_name>( \
404  static_cast<unsigned>(lhs) | static_cast<unsigned>(rhs)); \
405 } \
406  \
407 inline enum_name operator&(enum_name lhs, enum_name rhs) { \
408  return static_cast<enum_name>( \
409  static_cast<unsigned>(lhs) & static_cast<unsigned>(rhs)); \
410 } \
411  \
412 inline enum_name operator^(enum_name lhs, enum_name rhs) { \
413  return static_cast<enum_name>( \
414  static_cast<unsigned>(lhs) ^ static_cast<unsigned>(rhs)); \
415 } \
416  \
417 inline enum_name& operator|=(enum_name &lhs, enum_name rhs) { \
418  lhs = static_cast<enum_name>( \
419  static_cast<unsigned>(lhs) | static_cast<unsigned>(rhs)); \
420  return lhs; \
421 } \
422  \
423 inline enum_name& operator&=(enum_name &lhs, enum_name rhs) { \
424  lhs = static_cast<enum_name>( \
425  static_cast<unsigned>(lhs) & static_cast<unsigned>(rhs)); \
426  return lhs; \
427 } \
428  \
429 inline enum_name& operator^=(enum_name &lhs, enum_name rhs) { \
430  lhs = static_cast<enum_name>( \
431  static_cast<unsigned>(lhs) ^ static_cast<unsigned>(rhs)); \
432  return lhs; \
433 } \
434  \
435 inline enum_name operator~(enum_name rhs) { \
436  return static_cast<enum_name>(~static_cast<unsigned>(rhs)); \
437 } \

1349  format_tag aformat) {
1350  validate_dims(adims);
1351  error::wrap_c_api(mkldnn_memory_desc_init_by_tag(&data, (int)adims.size(),
1352  adims.size() == 0 ? nullptr : &adims[0],

1354  "could not initialize a memory descriptor");
1355  }

1363  validate_dims(adims);
1364  error::wrap_c_api(mkldnn_memory_desc_init_by_strides(&data,
1365  (int)adims.size(),
1366  adims.size() == 0 ? nullptr : &adims[0],
1367  convert_to_c(adata_type),
1368  astrides.size() == 0 ? nullptr : &astrides[0]),
1369  "could not initialize a memory descriptor");

1382  mkldnn_memory_desc_t sub_md;
1383  error::wrap_c_api(mkldnn_memory_desc_init_submemory(&sub_md,
1384  &data, &adims[0], &offsets[0]),
1385  "could not initialize a sub-memory");

1387  }

1391  size_t get_size() const { return mkldnn_memory_desc_get_size(&data); }

1394  return mkldnn_memory_desc_equal(&data, &other.data) != 0;
1395  }

1790 struct primitive_desc : public handle<mkldnn_primitive_desc_t> {
1791  primitive_desc() = default;
1792 
1796  primitive_desc(const_mkldnn_op_desc_t desc, const primitive_attr *attr,
1797  const engine &e, const_mkldnn_primitive_desc_t hint_fwd_pd) {
1798  mkldnn_primitive_desc_iterator_t iterator = nullptr;
1799  mkldnn_status_t status = mkldnn_primitive_desc_iterator_create(
1800  &iterator, desc, attr ? attr->get() : nullptr, e.get(),
1801  hint_fwd_pd);
1802  error::wrap_c_api(status,
1803  "could not create a primitive descriptor iterator");
1804  pd_iterator.reset(iterator);
1805  fetch_impl();
1806  }
1807 
1808  engine get_engine() { return engine::query(*this); }
1809 
1810  primitive_attr get_primitive_attr() const {
1811  const_mkldnn_primitive_attr_t const_cattr;
1812  error::wrap_c_api(mkldnn_primitive_desc_get_attr(get(), &const_cattr),
1813  "could not get attributes");
1814  mkldnn_primitive_attr_t cattr;
1815  error::wrap_c_api(mkldnn_primitive_attr_clone(&cattr, const_cattr),
1816  "could not clone attributes");
1817 
1818  primitive_attr attr;
1819  attr.reset(cattr);
1820  return attr;
1821  }
1822 
1824  const char *impl_info_str() const {
1825  const char *res;
1826  error::wrap_c_api(mkldnn_primitive_desc_query(get(),
1827  mkldnn_query_impl_info_str, 0, &res),
1828  "could not query implementation info string");
1829  return res;
1830  }
1831 
1833  memory::dim query_s64(query q) const {
1834  memory::dim res;
1835  mkldnn_status_t status = mkldnn_primitive_desc_query(get(),
1836  mkldnn::convert_to_c(q), 0, &res);
1837  return status == mkldnn_success ? res : 0;
1838  }
1839 
1846  bool next_impl() {
1847  mkldnn_status_t status = mkldnn_primitive_desc_iterator_next(
1848  pd_iterator.get());
1849  if (status == mkldnn_iterator_ends) return false;
1850  error::wrap_c_api(status, "primitive descriptor iterator next failed");
1851 
1852  fetch_impl();
1853  return true;
1854  }
1855 
1857  memory::desc query_md(query what, int idx = 0) const {
1858  std::vector<query> valid_q{ query::src_md, query::diff_src_md,
1859  query::weights_md, query::diff_weights_md, query::dst_md,
1860  query::diff_dst_md, query::workspace_md, query::scratchpad_md };
1861  if (!std::any_of(valid_q.cbegin(), valid_q.cend(),
1862  [=](query q) { return what == q; }))
1863  throw error(mkldnn_invalid_arguments, "invalid memory query");
1864 
1865  const mkldnn_memory_desc_t *cdesc = mkldnn_primitive_desc_query_md(
1866  get(), mkldnn::convert_to_c(what), idx);
1867  if (cdesc == nullptr) return memory::desc();
1868 
1869  return memory::desc(*cdesc);
1870  }
1871 
1875  memory::desc scratchpad_desc() const {
1876  return query_md(query::scratchpad_md, 0);
1877  }
1878 
1879  private:
1880  handle<mkldnn_primitive_desc_iterator_t> pd_iterator;
1881  void fetch_impl() {
1882  mkldnn_primitive_desc_t pd = mkldnn_primitive_desc_iterator_fetch(
1883  pd_iterator.get());
1884  error::wrap_c_api(pd != nullptr ? mkldnn_success : mkldnn_runtime_error,
1885  "could not fetch a primitive descriptor from the iterator");
1886  reset(pd);
1887  }
1888 };
